results.name: a(n)^3 is smallest cube containing exactly n 7's.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Cubic Number
mathematica: a[n_] := Module[{i = 0}, While[DigitCount[i^3][[7]] != n, i++ ]; i]; (* Sam Handler (sam_5_5_5_0(AT)yahoo.com), Aug 27 2006 *)
